                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3224: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-29T19:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1921—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 29—3:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>67. Your 44, January 27, 3 [<hi rend="italic">7</hi>] p.m. In view of collective
                    action consular body Canton described my 59, January 26, 11 a.m., Legation is
                    calling attention consul Canton to Legation’s September 5, 8 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >7</hi>] p.m., 1918, as indicating Department’s general attitude but not for
                    further individual action by him pending Department’s additional
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
